The paper focuses on training semantic part-based models of object classes from Google Images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and image retrieval. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning (ML) techniques to learn these models, specifically deep learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the models on a dataset, which involves metrics and performance analysis, falling under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of query-based image retrieval, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, falling under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
